# Local Coder 5090

On-device coding assistant for RTX 5090 / Windows 11 â€” ported from the DGX Spark (Qwen3-Coder-Next 80B / llama.cpp) to Ollama.

## What it is

A zero-cloud, zero-API-key coding loop running entirely on local hardware:

```
Browser UI â†’ local_coder_browser.py :8022 â†’ Ollama :11434 â†’ qwen3:32b
```

Same architecture as the Spark version:
- `python stdlib http.server` â€” no FastAPI, no extra deps
- `POST /chat` for inference
- `POST /coding/loop` â€” patch â†’ `git apply --check` â†’ `py_compile` â†’ `pytest`
- `POST /tools/run` â€” allowlisted shell tools
- `POST /patch` â€” check or apply unified diffs
- Training flywheel â€” every interaction logged to daily JSONL for future fine-tuning
- Per-project JSON memory
- MCP arcade server (35 tools) in `mcp/arcade/server.py`

## Hardware

| Component | Spec |
|-----------|------|
| GPU       | RTX 5090 32 GB VRAM |
| RAM       | 128 GB |
| OS        | Windows 11 |
| Python    | 3.12 |
| Backend   | Ollama (OpenAI-compat endpoint) |

## Models

| Role | Model | VRAM | Notes |
|------|-------|------|-------|
| Primary (coding + reasoning) | `qwen3:32b` | ~20 GB | Thinking model; token budget auto-reserves for `<think>` |
| Fast tier (quick completions) | `gemma4:latest` | ~5 GB | Gemma 4 edge (e4b), released Apr 2026, tool-calling + vision |
| Heavy (long-context analysis) | `llama3.1:70b` | ~28 GB | Optional; long-context work |

Model names are read from env (`LOCAL_CODER_MODEL`, `LOCAL_CODER_FAST_MODEL`) and
kept consistent across the server, `ops/`, config, and the service installer.

Pull models:
```
ollama pull qwen3:32b
ollama pull gemma4
```

## Quick start

```powershell
# 1. Clone
git clone https://github.com/rblake2320/local-coder-5090.git
cd local-coder-5090

# 2. Create workspace dir
mkdir C:\Users\techai\local-coder\workspace

# 3. Run (dev mode, opens browser)
python scripts\local_coder_browser.py

# 4. Or install as Windows service (Admin PowerShell)
.\install-service.ps1
```

Open `http://127.0.0.1:8022/` in your browser.

## Environment variables

Nothing is required for local-only use. See [`.env.example`](.env.example) for the full list; the essentials:

| Variable | Default | Purpose |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `LOCAL_CODER_MODEL_BASE` | `http://localhost:11434` | Ollama base URL |
| `LOCAL_CODER_MODEL` | `qwen3:32b` | Primary model |
| `LOCAL_CODER_FAST_MODEL` | `gemma4:latest` | Fast tier model |
| `LOCAL_CODER_HOME` | `C:\Users\techai\local-coder` | Root workspace |
| `LOCAL_CODER_WORKSPACE` | `$HOME\workspace` | Project workspace |
| `LOCAL_CODER_ALLOWED_ROOTS` | *(none)* | Extra dirs the tool sandbox may touch (`;`-separated) |
| `LOCAL_CODER_API_KEY` | *(none)* | If set, require matching `X-API-Key` header (server + CLI) |
| `LOCAL_CODER_RATE_LIMIT` / `_RATE_BURST` | `60` / `20` | Per-IP token-bucket rate limiting |
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | *(none)* | Enables OpenRouter fallback backend |
| `NVIDIA_API_KEY` | *(none)* | Enables NVIDIA NIM fallback backend |
| `BEDROCK_MODEL_ID` | `anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-â€¦` | AWS Bedrock fallback (needs `boto3`) |

## CLI

```powershell
# Status
python scripts\local_coder_cli.py status

# Chat
python scripts\local_coder_cli.py chat "explain this function"

# Coding loop
python scripts\local_coder_cli.py loop "fix the failing test" --patch fix.diff --apply

# Apply a patch
python scripts\local_coder_cli.py patch my_change.diff --cwd C:\my-project --apply
```

## Service management

```powershell
# Install
.\install-service.ps1

# Uninstall
.\install-service.ps1 -Uninstall

# Control
D:\tools\nssm\nssm.exe start LocalCoder
D:\tools\nssm\nssm.exe stop  LocalCoder

# Status / GPU
python ops\daily_control_win.py status
python ops\daily_control_win.py impact

# Unload all models (free VRAM)
python ops\daily_control_win.py model-mode off

# Pre-load primary model
python ops\daily_control_win.py model-mode on
```

## Testing & CI

Two suites:

- **Offline unit tests** (`tests/unit/`) â€” import the server module directly and
  exercise pure logic (path-traversal guards, upload-id validation, the tool
  allowlist, SSRF host blocking, circuit breaker, rate limiter, thinking-token
  reservation). No server or Ollama needed; these run in CI.
- **Live integration tests** (`tests/ops/`) â€” hit a running server on `:8022`.
  Marked `@pytest.mark.live` and deselected in CI.

```powershell
# Everything that runs without a server:
python -m pytest -m "not live" -q

# Full suite (start the server first):
python scripts\local_coder_browser.py --no-open
python -m pytest -q
```

Install dev tooling and run the exact CI checks locally:

```powershell
pip install -e ".[dev]"
ruff check .
python -m pytest -m "not live" -q
```

GitHub Actions (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) runs ruff + the offline suite on
Python 3.12 and 3.13 for every push and PR.

## Differences from Spark version

| | Spark (DGX GB10) | 5090 (Windows) |
|--|---|---|
| Model | Qwen3-Coder-Next 80B | deepseek-r1:32b |
| Backend | llama.cpp :8012 | Ollama :11434 |
| Fast tier | llama3.1:70b | gemma3:latest |
| Health check | `/health` | `/api/tags` |
| Service mgmt | systemd | NSSM |
| Python cmd | `python3` | `python` |
| Workspace | `/home/rblake2320/...` | `C:/Users/techai/...` |
| Deep context | 262k tokens | 131k tokens (32 GB VRAM) |

## Bug fixes vs original (from code review)

| # | Location | Fix |
|---|----------|-----|
| 1 | `_try_nvidia` | Returns `None` on HTTP error (was truthy error string; callers check `if result:`) |
| 2 | `ocr_extract_text` | Actually sends base64 image data in the model prompt |
| 3 | `has_corrections` | Changed `OR` to `AND`; old logic was almost always True |
| 4 | `call_bedrock_sync` | Wrapped in `run_in_executor` so it doesn't block the event loop |
| 5 | `try_local_inference` | Guards against missing `choices[]`; logs structural errors instead of silently swallowing |
| 6 | `FlywheelCollector.collect` | Single `datetime.now()` call so timestamp and filename can't be different days |
| 7 | `local_coder_tool_chat` | `isinstance(item, dict)` guard prevents double-wrapping tools |
| 8 | `list_specialists` | Guards against prompts with no second line after `Expertise:` header |
| 9 | Specialist functions | *(refactor pending â€” 8 copy-paste specialists â†’ factory loop)* |
| 10 | `LOCAL_MODEL_URL_2` | Removed hardcoded `spark2` hostname; requires explicit `$env:LOCAL_MODEL_URL_2` |

### Second review round (v0.3.0)

| # | Location | Fix |
|---|----------|-----|
| 11 | `local_coder_cli.py` | **Fatal `SyntaxError`** â€” `global BASE_URL` declared after use; CLI wouldn't run. Hoisted the declaration |
| 12 | `local_coder_cli.py` | Now sends `X-API-Key` from `LOCAL_CODER_API_KEY` (previously 401'd against an authed server) |
| 13 | `local_coder_cli.py` | HTTP errors surface status + server body instead of a bare `HTTP Error 500` |
| 14 | `server.py` OpenRouter map | `gemma4:latest` pointed at a Gemma 3 slug; corrected to `google/gemma-4-26b-a4b-it` (+ `gemma4:31b`, `gemma3` entries) |
| 15 | `server.py` `chkdsk_report` | Misleading multi-char `rstrip` on drive letter â†’ explicit letter extraction |
| 16 | `server.py` `decode_upload_content` | `raise â€¦ from None` to clarify exception chaining |
| 17 | `mcp/arcade/server.py` NIM retry | Returned `nvidia_error` while discarding the captured `last_error`; now surfaces the real reason |
| 18 | README / `install-service.ps1` / `ops/` | Model names unified on `qwen3:32b` + `gemma4:latest` (installer previously launched a different model than the code defaults) |
| 19 | Repo-wide | Added `pyproject.toml`, GitHub Actions CI, `.env.example`, and a 62-test offline unit suite; ruff-clean |

